article.description: Nana Foulland scored 15 points and blocked three shots and Bucknell rallied in the second half to beat Loyola (Md.) 67-58 on Wednesday night for the Greyhounds' fourth straight loss.
article.headline: Bucknell rallies to beat Loyola (Md.) 67-58 behind Foulland
article.linkText: Bucknell rallies to beat Loyola (Md.) 67-58 behind Foulland
article.story: BALTIMORE, Md. -- Nana Foulland scored 15 points and blocked three shots and Bucknell rallied in the second half to beat Loyola (Md.) 67-58 on Wednesday night for the Greyhounds' fourth straight loss. Zach Thomas, Stephen Brown and Ryan Frazier scored 11 points apiece for the Bison (9-9, 6-1 Patriot League), who made 23 of 37 free throws and scored 23 points on 16 Loyola turnovers. Trailing by one at halftime, Bucknell rallied with an 11-2 run and led 38-36 on Brown's layup. Cam Gregory's layup and free throw gave Loyola a 42-41 lead with 12:36 to go before Bucknell pulled ahead on an 11-2 run and led 62-51 on Brown's jumper with 3:17 left. The Greyhounds outscored the Bison 7-5 from there, but couldn't catch up. Franz Rassman and Jarred Jones scored 14 points each for Loyola (4-14, 3-4) and Gregory added 12 with 12 rebounds.
